dod-digital-engineering pack — content licence
===============================================

This pack is derived from:
    Digital Engineering Strategy
    US Department of Defense, Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of
    Defense for Systems Engineering (ODASD(SE)), Office of the Under Secretary
    of Defense for Research and Engineering (OUSD R&E), June 2018

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work, 17 U.S.C. 105); Distribution
Statement A — Approved for public release; distribution is unlimited.
(tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the US
Department of Defense, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in the
United States (17 U.S.C. 105). It carries Distribution Statement A (approved for
public release; distribution unlimited). It is in the public domain: anyone may
reproduce, transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially,
without permission.

Attribution to the US Department of Defense and ODASD(SE) is provided as a courtesy
(see the repository NOTICE), not a legal obligation. The DoD does not endorse this
pack or its authors.

CAVEAT: The Strategy itself is the only source used here. The related Digital
Engineering Body of Knowledge (DEBoK) is CAC-gated (not publicly available) and is
intentionally NOT used or reproduced in this pack. The Strategy is a non-prescriptive
vision document; this pack carries no implementation-plan or step-by-step procedural
content beyond what the public Strategy states.

